Are added fees crippling your investments?
For every new client, we provide a free investment audit to expose the true cost of owning each of your investments. If there are hidden fees, we bring them to light. Nine times out of ten, your investment costs with The Mather Group are significantly lower.
Get a Free Cost Audit 









A FIDUCIARY OBLIGATION TOPUT YOUR INTERESTS FIRST
Fiduciaries like The Mather Group are registered investment advisors (RIAs) with a fiduciary duty to their clients.
That means we have a legal obligation to always act in your best interest. Brokers and hybrid RIAs are not obligated to act in your best interest and can sell investment products for commissions.
And there are no conflicts about where your money is held – all your investments are held in a separate custody with Fidelity, a highly rated national firm. 

Our motivation is to see your retirement investments grow.
Meet Your Advisors 








Only 3.8% of all advisors areOBLIGATED TO PUT YOUR INTERESTS FIRST†
Is your financial advisor truly your advocate?  Conduct a quick "Fiduciary Audit" on any firm you might consider. 







Critical questions to ask your advisor



Do you offer in-house/proprietary investment products or solutions? This identifies conflicts of interest. If they use their own products, they are double dipping, which means they are charging you product fees on top of management fees.
The Mather Group has an open architecture, which means we can invest in anything that is publicly traded. We only use what is best for our clients and we DO NOT have our own products. 

Do you carry a series 6 or series 7 license? This identifies if someone carries a brokerage license. If they do, they are not a fiduciary 100% of the time and can get paid in non-transparent ways.
The Mather Group does not hold a series 6 or series 7 license since we are a true fiduciary RIA.
Click here to see if your advisor is a broker: http://brokercheck.finra.org 


